modules.description: This module handles the registration and execution of database migrations specifically for PostgreSQL. It provides functions to register individual migrations or lists of migrations, execute them asynchronously, and run all registered migrations. Concrete use cases include setting up or updating database schemas during application startup or deployment.

This module implements session management using PostgreSQL as the backend. It provides functions to create sessions, set and retrieve session values, and find sessions by identifier. Use cases include storing user authentication tokens, managing temporary session data, and persisting user state across requests.

This module handles database migrations specifically for MariaDB sessions. It provides functions to register individual or multiple migration tasks, execute them asynchronously, and manage their lifecycle within a container. Use it to set up or update session-related database schemas in MariaDB environments.

This module implements session management using MariaDB as the backend. It provides functions to create sessions, set and retrieve session values, and find sessions by identifier. Use cases include storing user authentication data or temporary state in web applications.

This module handles session management and database migrations for PostgreSQL and MariaDB. It provides functions to create, retrieve, and manipulate sessions, as well as register and execute schema migrations. Concrete use cases include storing user authentication tokens in PostgreSQL and managing session state in MariaDB environments.
